&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate, Focus Investment Partners will support the firm’s private equity and venture capital fundraising platform through a combination of operational execution, investor servicing, administrative coordination, and project management responsibilities. Working closely with senior team members, this individual will help drive the day-to-day execution behind fundraising processes, investor communications, reporting, onboarding, and relationship management activities while gaining exposure to private markets and institutional fundraising.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for an early-career professional with experience or interest in investment operations, private funds, investor relations, or fundraising support who is highly organized, detail-oriented, self-sufficient, and eager to learn. The position requires someone who can quickly absorb internal processes, proactively ask questions, and ultimately take ownership of recurring workflows and operational responsibilities with minimal oversight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The near-term focus of the role is execution-heavy operational support across fundraising and investor servicing activities, with longer-term growth opportunities into investor relations, diligence support, fundraising strategy, and business development.&lt;/p&gt;
