&lt;li&gt;Coordinate investor meetings, conference participation, fundraising events, and internal team activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare meeting materials, fundraising presentations, investor communications, reporting packages, and organizational materials for internal and external use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage investor records, CRM updates, fundraising pipelines, relationship management documentation, and internal tracking systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with investor onboarding, subscription documentation, close trackers, due diligence requests, data room access, and ongoing investor information requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and follow up with third-party administrators, custodians, platforms, and service providers (including CAIS, Ultimus, and similar partners) to support fundraising and onboarding workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a point person for existing client relationships by responding to inquiries, coordinating follow-ups, resolving operational issues, and ensuring a high level of responsiveness and service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track fundraising activity, investor engagement, outstanding action items, and key business development initiatives across the platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support senior team members by coordinating follow-up actions, maintaining project timelines, and ensuring operational workflows are executed efficiently and accurately.&lt;/li&gt;
